The Vice President of the United States held meetings with faith leaders, refugee advocates, and members of the "Bibles, Badges and Business" coalition to discuss the influx of unaccompanied minors migrating to the southwest border and immigration reform. In the meeting with faith leaders and refugee advocates, the Vice President discussed the Administration's efforts to address the humanitarian situation caused by the influx of children and adults migrating primarily from Central America. He also shared the outcomes of his meeting with the presidents of Guatemala and El Salvador, as well as representatives from Honduras and Mexico, which included a commitment to combat misinformation spread by criminal networks and address the underlying causes of migration. In the meeting with members of "Bibles, Badges, and Business," the Vice President expressed gratitude for their leadership in advocating for immigration reform and encouraged them to continue their efforts.